title.narrative: PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION AND FINANCE FOR CHILDREN

description.narrative: Output 1.2 Social sector ministries and parliament have improved capacity to manage and oversight public finance for children, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Reducing Child Poverty, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, the state has effective and accountable public administration system to deliver results for disadvantaged children

title.narrative: Output 1.2 Social sector ministries and parliament have improved capacity to manage and oversight public finance for children

description.narrative: Multidimensional measurement and analysis of child poverty are fully embedded in the country’s official statistics. The NSC started regular reporting on both child monetary and multidimensional deprivations in the national SDG monitoring system platform and flagship publication ‘Living Standards of the Population’. UNICEF’s consistent engagement and joint advocacy with partners contributed to the strengthening of social sector priorities in the 2021–2026 National Development Programme (NDP), including improvement of social protection coverage of young children, doubling pre-school coverage with variability of ECE services, and alignment of national and sectoral planning, budgeting and spending. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
